Slice the @sugar snap peas{80%grams} in half lengthways.

Trim and peel the @carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the
length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Unconventional Plant-Based Burgers{2} to the pan.

Use a #spoon{} to mash into a mince-like texture as it cooks. Cook until browned,
~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Ensure they're piping
hot throughout.

While the veggie mince browns, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with
@salt{1/2%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{125%grams} to the water and bring back
to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking
together.

Once the veggie mince has browned, add the sugar snaps, @red Thai style paste{50%grams}
and garlic to the pan.

Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @ketjap manis{50%grams}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{75%milliliters} for
the sauce (see pantry for both amounts) to the pan. Stir to combine and bring
to the boil.

Add the cooked noodles and carrot ribbons. Toss to coat, adding a splash of
water to loosen if needed. Remove from the heat.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

When ready, share the veggie mince noodle stir-fry between your #bowls{}.
Enjoy!